#Setting up ESP32 with Arduino
1-	Install Arduino IDE
2-	Then in your Arduino IDE, go to File --> Preferences
3-	Enter the following into the “Additional Board Manager URLs” field:
https://raw.githubusercontent.com/espressif/arduino-esp32/gh-pages/package_esp32_index.json
4-	Then, click the “OK” button:
5-	Go and open the Boards Manager. Go to Tools --> Board --> Boards Manager…
6-	Search for ESP32 and press install button for the “ESP32 by Espressif Systems“:
#Testing the installation
1.	Select your Board in Tools > Board menu
2.	Select the Port
3.	Open the example under File --> Examples
--> WiFi(ESP32) > WiFiScan
4.	A new sketch opens in your Arduino IDE
5.	Press the Upload button in the Arduino IDE
6.	If it work correctly  you should see a “Done uploading.”
7.	Open the Arduino IDE Serial Monitor at a baud rate of 115200
8.	Press the ESP32 on-board Enable button and you should see the networks available near your ESP32


